83.5	Kilometre	Kilometre	The kilometre is a unit of length in the metric system, equal to one thousand metres (kilo- being the SI prefix for 1000). It is now the measurement unit used officially for expressing distances between geographical places on land in most of the world; notable exceptions are the United States and the United Kingdom where the statute mile is the official unit used.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/12/Niag715.jpg/200px-Niag715.jpg
